==English==

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-aɪvən|-aɪvən]]

===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

# {{transitive}} To make somebody or something more [[lively]] or [[interesting]].
#: ''The game was much enlivened when both teams scored within five minutes of each other.''
# {{transitive}} To make something [[brighter]], [[sprightly]] or more [[cheerful]].
#: ''A few more pictures on the wall would enliven this room.''
# To give [[life]], [[action]], or [[spirit]] to

